An interface is a blueprint of a class that is used to achieve abstraction and multiple inheritance.
It contains abstract methods (by default) and defines what a class must do, not how it does it.

interface Payment {
    void pay();   // abstract method
}

class UpiPayment implements Payment {
    public void pay() {
        System.out.println("Payment done using UPI");
    }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Payment p = new UpiPayment();
        p.pay();
    }
}
